{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fdf4ab3e-a733-43b3-9f58-904a39ebaddf","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Filter syntax** — MTP doesn't use VSTest's `&` operator. Use `/` to AND conditions, and the property for traits is different:\n\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `&` (AND) | `/` (AND) |\n| `|` (OR) | `\\|` (OR) |\n| `Property~Value` (contains) | same |\n| `Category=Smoke` (trait) | same |\n\n**2. Runner flag** — You already have `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` set, so `dotnet test` will route through MTP. Good.\n\n**Updated CI command:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe only change is `&` → `/`. The `~` (contains) operator and `Category=Smoke` trait syntax remain the same under MTP.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe8a8fc4-bb75-4f8c-8cc7-5b524fa6c67b","outputTokens":287,"requestId":"0420:1CF5FA:1E15C31:21F1F3F:69E81B67"},"id":"2caedc63-9906-467f-8fbf-2667a3672821","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:50:55.438Z","parentId":"32013db8-0254-4b89-aba2-323775fc943d"}
